  <subsection xml:id="sec-deriv-fxn-subsection-BC">
    <title>Before Class <!-- - Hour 1 --></title>

    <exploration xml:id="ex-deriv-fxn-name1">
      <title>Graphing the Derivative of a Quadratic Function</title>
      <p>
        This graphical exploration walks students through how to use the slopes of the graph of a quadratic function to
        graph the function's derivative, reinforcing the idea that the derivative is itself a function with inputs and outputs.   
        <!-- A draft of the text and images for the animation/video can be found <url href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1p_egMo87QQ1HR2pNyAiIv-ldE06jOlqWdbKHRgpZJrk/edit?usp=sharing">in this Google document</url>.   -->
      </p>
      <p>Learning objectives for this activity<fn>
        <ul>
          <li>
            use the <em>slopes</em> of <m>f(x)</m> to identify the <em>heights, or values,</em> of <m>f'(x)</m>
          </li>
          <li>
            find where the roots of <m>f'(x)</m> are by looking at a graph of <m>f(x)</m>
          </li>
          <li>
            view the derivative as a function with inputs and outputs
          </li>
        </ul>
      </fn>.
      </p>
         <interactive xml:id="doenet-interactive-exercise-deriv-fxn-name1" platform="doenetml" width="100%" aspect="2.1:5">
          <slate surface="doenetml">
            <xi:include href="./exercises/doenet/ex-deriv-fxn-name1.ptx" parse="text"/>
          </slate>   
        </interactive>  
    </exploration>

  <exploration xml:id="ex-deriv-fxn-name2">
    <title>Graphing the Derivative of a More Complicated Function</title>
    <p>
      This graphical exploration leads students to identify key features of the graph of a function and see how those translate to the
      graph of the function's derivative, reinforcing the idea that the derivative is itself a function with inputs and outputs.   
      <!-- A draft of the text and images for the animation/video can be found <url href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1p_egMo87QQ1HR2pNyAiIv-ldE06jOlqWdbKHRgpZJrk/edit?usp=sharing">in this Google document</url>.   -->
    </p>
    <p>Learning objectives for this activity<fn>
      <ul>
        <li>
          use the <em>slopes</em> of <m>f(x)</m> to identify the sign of the <em>heights, or values,</em> of <m>f'(x)</m>
        </li>
        <li>
          find where the roots of <m>f'(x)</m> are by looking at a graph of <m>f(x)</m>
        </li>
        <li>
          view the derivative as a function with inputs and outputs
        </li>
      </ul>
    </fn>.
    </p>
